          <fr:mainmatter>
            <fr:p>A Hilbert space is a complete <fr:link type="local" href="FA-002M.xml" addr="FA-002M" title="Inner Product">inner product space</fr:link>.</fr:p>
            <fr:p>Hilbert spaces extend the methods of vector algebra and calculus from 2D and 3D Euclidean spaces to spaces with any finite or infinite number of dimensions.</fr:p>
            <fr:p>Key properties include:</fr:p>
            <fr:ul><fr:li>Every Hilbert space is a <fr:link type="local" href="FA-002I.xml" addr="FA-002I" title="Banach Space">Banach space</fr:link>, with the norm derived from the inner product</fr:li>
